DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T081000Z
DTEND:20260323T083500Z
SUMMARY:Federated llm-d: Elevating Distributed Inference Beyond Cluster Boundaries - Madhuri Yechuri\, Elotl & Abhishek Malvankar\, IBM
DESCRIPTION:.As generative AI models trend towards becoming commodity\, the ability to serve them in a cost-effective high-performant fashion across hardware accelerators impacts time to market for Enterprise AI Initiatives. Llm-d is a popular open-source AI Framework that meets this exact need. \n \nModels are sensitive to hardware accelerators. Hardware accelerators are expensive and in short supply. Model serving time cannot and should not be impacted by unavailability of desired accelerator in a given Kubernetes cluster. The desired accelerator might just be a hop away in a different cluster in same/different region in same/different cloud. It would be prudent to source accelerators from all available clusters to deliver state-of-the-art performance to meet Enterprise SLAs. \n \nThis talk presents a federated llm-d framework which stretches llm-d across multiple clusters. We will discuss use cases for federated distributed inference\, and present a blueprint for the federated stack along with a demo.
CATEGORIES:CLOUD NATIVE AI + KUBEFLOW DAY
LOCATION:Hall 7 | Room B\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:61d0e0e9c862683cadbc0f2a49f6a46b
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/61d0e0e9c862683cadbc0f2a49f6a46b
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T081000Z
DTEND:20260323T083500Z
SUMMARY:The Shift: Radio Network Functions as IT Applications - Guillaume Nevicato\, Orange & Andre Puschmann\, Software Radio Systems
DESCRIPTION:The telco industry has been on a cloudification journey for over a decade. In the context of Radio Access Networks (RAN)\, this deep transformation is primarily driven by Open RAN initiatives.\nThis talk illustrates how RAN is gradually evolving towards IT architecture.\n\nKey synergies between Sylva and OCUDU open-source projects are driving this transformation:\n* Sylva provides a telco-grade cloud stack\, enabling scalable and reliable cloud infrastructure.\n* OCUDU focuses on developing network functions with full adoption of cloud-native patterns\, fostering innovation and interoperability.\n\nFocusing then on O-Cloud\, the cloud layer of Open RAN\, Sylva is proposing an ambitious approach with Cluster Template description based on Cluster API\, delivering a full declarative approach.\n\nA live demo will showcase a FluxCD GitOps deployment of an Open RAN Distributed Unit (DU) network function on Sylva Telco Cloud\, relying on IT deployment workflows in a multi nodes architecture.
CATEGORIES:CLOUD NATIVE TELCO DAY
LOCATION:G104-105\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:b552d8dd7409877a18ccf067755264ec
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/b552d8dd7409877a18ccf067755264ec
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T081000Z
DTEND:20260323T083500Z
SUMMARY:Vibe Coding Meets GitOps - Stefan Prodan\, ControlPlane
DESCRIPTION:With vibe coding taking center stage in modern development\, it is just a matter of time before vibe deployments and AI-driven operations become an accepted practice in the DevOps space.\n\nIn this session\, Stefan will discuss the collision between vibe coding's rapid iteration and GitOps's discipline of declarative\, auditable infrastructure.\n\nHe will explore how teams can leverage Flux MCP and AI Agents to generate\, manage and troubleshoot GitOps pipelines\, enabling faster deployments while maintaining control and security.\n\nThe session concludes with the Flux MCP roadmap and opportunities for community contribution.
CATEGORIES:FLUXCON
LOCATION:Elicium 1\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:37e6798462301cd437eac07d0ce27822
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/37e6798462301cd437eac07d0ce27822
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T081000Z
DTEND:20260323T083500Z
SUMMARY:Feeding the Cloud: Designing Data-Driven Robotics Systems - Nina Polshakova\, Solo.io & Aaron Ray\, MIT
DESCRIPTION:You might imagine a robot as a standalone entity\, like R2-D2\, with all processing onboard. In reality\, modern robotics systems often send vast amounts of data to cloud backends for processing and training\, involving complex networking and distributed computing.\n\nWhile edge devices and IoT also combine cloud and local computation\, robots face unpredictable connectivity\, requiring failover to local compute and smaller models. Determining which computations should run on-device versus in the cloud presents rich research opportunities\, and distributing computation adds networking and orchestration complexity. Effective system design must carefully balance the efficiency of local computation with the greater power of cloud-based reasoning.\n\nThis session explores how cloud-native\, distributed architectures can coordinate edge and cloud computation to enable reliable\, intelligent robotics in real-world environments.
CATEGORIES:KUBERNETES ON EDGE DAY
LOCATION:Emerald Room\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:2a2766a7561fa5358e473e03c13c3a80
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/2a2766a7561fa5358e473e03c13c3a80
END:VEVENT
