DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T084000Z
DTEND:20260323T084500Z
SUMMARY:Cloud Native AI + Kubeflow Day | Sponsored Keynote: Building Your AI Factory: Where Data Science and Platform Engineering Meet - Andreea Munteanu\, Spectro Cloud
DESCRIPTION:AI adoption at scale requires more than great models. It forces enterprises to rethink how their operational practices support specialized hardware\, integrated tooling across the ML lifecycle\, and enhanced security measures to protect sensitive data in an automated and reliable manner. Platform engineers and data scientists naturally focus on different areas. There is a natural skill gap between platform maintainers and end users\, creating risks such as underutilized resources\, overly complex architectures\, and fragile day 2 operations. Layered on top are stringent security and compliance requirements for every component of the solution.\n\nIn this session\, we explore how cloud-native architectures and Kubernetes-based platforms provide the foundation for building AI factories that are scalable\, modular\, and fully automated. We’ll break down the essential components of an AI factory and explain how they can be easily consumed in a self-service manner across different use cases\, such as model deployment. We will share lessons learned from real-world deployments\, highlighting what works\, what doesn’t\, and how teams have adapted their architectures and processes along the way.
CATEGORIES:CLOUD NATIVE AI + KUBEFLOW DAY
LOCATION:Hall 7 | Room B\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:f853112599ab7a8e238c52df9c653eb3
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/f853112599ab7a8e238c52df9c653eb3
