SUMMARY:Open Source SecurityCon | Sponsored Keynote: From Packets to Pods: Lessons from 25 Years of Open Source Visibility - Gerald Combs\, Sysdig
DESCRIPTION:Before we had "observability" or "cloud native\," we had packets. Gerald Combs\, creator of Wireshark\, reflects on nearly three decades of maintaining one of the world’s most ubiquitous open-source tools. In this keynote\, Gerald shares the truth about building a community that lasts: why visibility is still the cornerstone of security\, and how the lessons of the past are the only way to secure the complex\, ephemeral future of Kubernetes.
CATEGORIES:OPEN SOURCE SECURITYCON
LOCATION:Hall 8 | Room D\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
