DTSTART:20260323T091000Z
DTEND:20260323T091500Z
SUMMARY:Observability Day | Sponsored Keynote - Before You Let AI Touch Production: Autoremediation Readiness - Colleen White\, Chronosphere
DESCRIPTION:The promise of autoremediation is alluring: through the magic of AI\, you &nbsp\;won’t just find issues faster\; you’ll resolve them automatically\, with nothing left to do &nbsp\;but validate and observe. MTTR becomes obsolete because issues are fixed as they occur. \n\nBut jumping to this step without a solid foundation of data\, curation\, and policy is like getting a bad pour from the taps - all froth\, no beer. \n\nClosed-loop remediation isn’t magic. It’s the final stage in disciplined\, AI-driven observability workflow.\n\nIn this talk\, we’ll cover the three essential steps to making autoremediation safe and effective: \n\n- Comprehensive system coverage at scale\n- Usable\, navigable data\n- Rules of the road for autoremediation\n\nYou’ll leave with a practical checklist to evaluate your organization’s readiness and framework for deciding how and where autoremediation should (and shouldn’t) be applied. \n\nNo hype. Just the work required before AI earns the right to act in production.
CATEGORIES:OBSERVABILITY DAY
LOCATION:Forum (Ground Floor)\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
