DTEND:20260323T094000Z
SUMMARY:GitOps and Secrets: State of the Union - Kostis Kapelonis\, Octopus Deploy
DESCRIPTION:One of the most popular questions for people adopting GitOps is what to do with secrets. Argo CD version 3.x finally has a clear recommendation on how to handle secrets with Kubernetes. More specifically\, the new proposal is to externalize secret management entirely instead of using plugins or other similar mechanisms to inject secrets during application deployment.\n\nIn this talk we will reevaluate and compare all the popular secret solutions (sealed-secrets\, sops\, vault-plugin\, external-secret-operator\, csi-drivers\, etc.) and explain where they differ and the pros/cons of each.\n\nWe will also explain the common pitfalls of using secrets with Argo CD and discuss the best practices for good secret hygiene\, such as secret rotation and storage.
CATEGORIES:ARGOCON
LOCATION:G102-103\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:706243a582642bbd3f79e899b489394c
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/706243a582642bbd3f79e899b489394c
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T091500Z
DTEND:20260323T092000Z
SUMMARY:Cloud Native Telco Day l Sponsored Keynote: Telco’s Next Act: Scaling Intelligence with Open Source and Agentic AI - Ranny Haiby\, The Linux Foundation & Philippe Ensarguet\, Orange
DESCRIPTION:For about a decade\, the telco industry has been perfecting the “Cloud-Native” playbook—moving from rigid hardware to flexible\, software-defined ecosystems. But as we move into 2026\, agility is no longer enough\; we need autonomy. This keynote explores the industry’s next chapter of moving from cloud-native foundations to an Agentic-AI-Native future.\n\nWe’ll look at the big picture: how the next generation of networks will transition from running on code to “thinking” through autonomous agents. Discover why an open-source-first strategy is the essential bridge for this transition\, ensuring that as our networks become smarter\, they remain open\, interoperable\, and ready for the era of self-healing infrastructure.
CATEGORIES:CLOUD NATIVE TELCO DAY
LOCATION:G104-105\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:8e9cdc7c59287d377d1e67e1e099cb2b
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/8e9cdc7c59287d377d1e67e1e099cb2b
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T091500Z
DTEND:20260323T092000Z
SUMMARY:KeycloakCon | Sponsored Keynote: Modernizing Railway IT Architecture: Secure-by-Design with Keycloak - Bernhard Denner\, Hitatchi Rail
DESCRIPTION:Mission-critical railway management systems are increasingly interconnected\, making cybersecurity more essential than ever.\nWe\, at Hitachi Rail\, have therefore rebuilt our products using secure-by-design principles\, with Keycloak serving as a central component of our architecture.\nKeycloak has also supported us in modernizing the operation and maintenance of our IT systems\, running these management systems in the customers data-centers.\nRegulations such as NIS2 and the CRA confirm that we are well positioned for the challenges ahead.\n&nbsp\;\nThis talk highlights some IEC 62443-4-2 requirements that often challenge traditional IT architectures\, and demonstrates how Keycloak addresses them effectively.\nAlthough Keycloak alone does not guarantee full compliance\, it plays a key role in realizing resilient\, modern secure-by-design architectures.\n\n
CATEGORIES:KEYCLOAKCON
LOCATION:Hall 7 | Room A\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:85f17006f089b77047c16c57aeed2907
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/85f17006f089b77047c16c57aeed2907
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T091500Z
DTEND:20260323T092000Z
SUMMARY:Kubernetes on Edge Day | Sponsored Keynote: Edge AI in Practice: Lessons from Production Environments - Saad Malik\, Spectro Cloud
DESCRIPTION:As AI workloads move closer to users\, devices\, and data sources\, the edge has become the next proving ground — yet expectations often outpace operational reality. Drawing on insights from a recently released industry research paper on Edge AI\, this talk explores what is actually happening as teams deploy and operate AI at the edge.\nWe’ll walk through real-world data on infrastructure constraints\, workload placement decisions\, model lifecycle management\, and operational tradeoffs observed across production edge environments. The session examines where Kubernetes-based approaches enable progress\, where they introduce friction\, and how architectures are evolving to support reliable\, scalable AI inference beyond the datacenter.\nThe talk focuses on recurring patterns and practical considerations that are shaping current edge AI deployments and influencing how teams think about future designs.
CATEGORIES:KUBERNETES ON EDGE DAY
LOCATION:Emerald Room\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:72ceaec22d18eabbbd117e761fd4e183
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/72ceaec22d18eabbbd117e761fd4e183
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T092000Z
DTEND:20260323T092500Z
SUMMARY:BackstageCon | Sponsored Keynote - Building an IDP in 5 Minutes Not 5 Months - Matar Peles\, Port
DESCRIPTION:Building an internal developer portal used to take months. Weeks of scoping\, sprints of plugin development\, endless YAML configurations\, and a dedicated team just to get a service catalog live. By the time it shipped\, half the requirements had changed.\n\nWhat if you could do it in minutes?\n\nIn this session\, I’ll build a fully functional developer portal live on stage - from an empty screen to a working platform - using nothing but natural language prompts. A service catalog mapped to real infrastructure\, self-service actions with manual approvals\, dashboards tracking engineering standards\, and custom logic tailored to how your organization works.\n\nBut that’s just the foundation for what comes next.\n\nDeveloper portals are evolving from dashboards engineers look at into platforms that act on their behalf. Once your portal understands your services\, ownership model\, and standards\, it has the context to power agentic workflows that go beyond a UI. I’ll show that progression live: from catalog\, to self-service\, to an agentic workflow that triages and resolves an incident on its own.\nWhether you’re running Backstage\, evaluating alternatives\, or starting from scratch - you’ll walk away with a concrete picture of where developer portals are headed\, how fast you can get there\, and what “agentic” actually looks like when it’s not just a buzzword.
CATEGORIES:BACKSTAGECON
LOCATION:Hall 8 | Room E\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:efb0cfa00f2dadce5a54184c8195d96a
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/efb0cfa00f2dadce5a54184c8195d96a
