SUMMARY:May the Flux Be With You: Tales From the GitOps Trenches at NatWest - Joel King & Lee Coupe\, NatWest Group
DESCRIPTION:In a galaxy not so far away (actually\, inside a major UK bank)\, two Principal Engineers from NatWest’s Platform as a Product (PaaP) team have been battling the forces of managing GitOps at scale in a regulated environment. Their weapon of choice? Flux.\n\nThis insight-packed session will share experiences of using Flux to scale GitOps across multiple complex and multi-tenanted Kubernetes platforms.\n\nFrom deploying and managing NatWest's PaaP control plane with Kratix and Flux to scheduling customer deployments with the Flux Operator’s new Time Based deployments\, attendees will learn how GitOps can become a force for good.\n\nThe session also explores how NatWest keep CVEs in check by evergreening Flux Operator and Controller container images\, because nothing ruins a Jedi’s day like a critical vulnerability!
CATEGORIES:FLUXCON
LOCATION:Elicium 1\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:8034d883d7dbeec9a6127668cdb0ad9a
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/8034d883d7dbeec9a6127668cdb0ad9a
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T092500Z
DTEND:20260323T093000Z
SUMMARY:Kubernetes on Edge Day | Sponsored Keynote: Edge AI: Because the Cloud is Too Slow and the World is Too Big - Said Ouissal\, ZEDEDA
DESCRIPTION:Edge AI is transforming operations by bringing inference and AI agents closer to where data is generated. From real-time decisions on factory floors to low-latency insights in retail\, energy\, and transportation\, running AI at the edge enables faster responses\, lower bandwidth costs\, and increased resilience. However\, operating AI across highly distributed\, resource-constrained environments introduces significant complexity. This session explores how Kubernetes is a critical foundation for running AI at the edge\, enabling consistent deployment\, orchestration\, and lifecycle management of AI agents and workloads across thousands of locations while maintaining reliability and security. Through real-world examples\, Said will highlight proven architectures\, best practices\, and common pitfalls when combining edge AI and Kubernetes\, equipping teams to confidently operationalize AI at the edge.
CATEGORIES:KUBERNETES ON EDGE DAY
LOCATION:Emerald Room\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
