DTEND:20260323T112500Z
SUMMARY:Panel: Kubernetes Networking: Present and Future - Gergely Csatari\, Nokia; Lionel Jouin\, Red Hat; Antonio Ojea\, Google; Surya Seetharaman\, Red Hat
DESCRIPTION:Networking in Kubernetes is critical for telecom workloads. The available capabilities and solutions in the platform dictate what kind of capabilities can be built on top. In the last years work started to revolutionize how networks can be consumed in Kubernetes\, but at the same time the current solutions are deployed in all telecom cloud solutions. With the increasing amount of AI workloads the networking demand for Kubernetes is changing what can alter expectations of telecom workloads. In this constant state of flux our panel aims to show what is the state of Kubernetes networking in 2026 and what are the foreseeable future directions.\n\nThis panel of distinguished experts of Kubernetes networking will discuss the current state of Kubernetes networking and the areas of development. We will explore the evolution options of the topic for the next 1 – 5of years and share our vision on how Kubernetes networks will be consumed in 2031.
CATEGORIES:CLOUD NATIVE TELCO DAY
LOCATION:G104-105\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:9c190f69189574e2927481cc3ceb43a8
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/9c190f69189574e2927481cc3ceb43a8
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T105000Z
DTEND:20260323T112500Z
SUMMARY:Panel: It’s Not If\, It’s When - Practical Preparation for the Next Software Supply Chain Attack - Hannah Foxwell & Justin Cormack\, Independent; Sal Kimmich\, GadflyAI; Erika Heidi\, Chainguard; Josh Bressers\, Anchore
DESCRIPTION:Do you remember your first zero-day? How about the most recent? Who was involved in the response? What tools did they use? How long did it take to patch that CVE? Are you confident you didn’t miss anything?\n\nMost security teams are outnumbered by developers by factors of hundreds or even thousands to one. Many organisations don’t have a single security specialist\, delegating that role to their infrastructure or platform teams.\n\nWhen asking these teams about how prepared they feel for the next supply chain attack or zero-day CVE the answer is always the same: “We’re f***ed”\n\nOur expert panel is here to help. Bringing deep expertise in security\, platform engineering and cloud native we’re going to get practical and tactical about how to plan for the next zero-day.\n\nBecause it’s not if\, it’s when. We need to be ready.
CATEGORIES:OPEN SOURCE SECURITYCON
LOCATION:Hall 8 | Room D\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:e41bbc24548f4d7604ff69e15d491d2c
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/e41bbc24548f4d7604ff69e15d491d2c
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T110000Z
DTEND:20260323T111000Z
SUMMARY:⚡Lightning Talk: Flux-Powered Bootstrapping a Kubernetes With GitOps and CaC - Paris Nakita Kejser\, Astrona
DESCRIPTION:Explore how to use Flux as a GitOps-driven bootstrap engine for Kubernetes clusters\, orchestrating both foundational infrastructure and application layers. Starting with Configuration as Code (CaC) powered by Ansible.\n\nThen\, we'll dive into how Flux can take over the second stage: managing higher-layer workloads\, microservices\, and platform applications using GitOps principles.\n\nWhether you’re bootstrapping a production-grade cluster or designing internal platform tooling\, this session will provide a real-world\, flexible architecture that unifies Ansible\, Flux\, and GitOps into one powerful lifecycle.
CATEGORIES:FLUXCON
LOCATION:Elicium 1\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:f0065591d37f307fe14e617e0e630993
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/f0065591d37f307fe14e617e0e630993
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T110000Z
DTEND:20260323T111000Z
SUMMARY:⚡Lightning Talk: Keycloak and EUDI-Wallet: A Match Made in Heaven? - Dominik Schlosser\, Freelancer
DESCRIPTION:The EU Digital Identity Wallet is coming and will soon allow EU citizens to authenticate to government services using a standardized and decentralized wallet infrastructure. Keycloak\, as one of the most widely used IAM solutions\, is expected to support this and has long begun to implement the necessary standards like OpenID 4 Verifiable Credentials Issuance (OpenID4VCI).\nLast year\, one of my public services customers asked me to use what is already there\, enhance it and implement a first working wallet authentication prototype inside Keycloak.\nThis talk will showcase the results\, problems and future work.
CATEGORIES:KEYCLOAKCON
LOCATION:Hall 7 | Room A\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:916052f8f68d7baa1d163c8c853d16ca
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/916052f8f68d7baa1d163c8c853d16ca
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T111500Z
DTEND:20260323T114000Z
SUMMARY:Sylva\, Taming Complexity With FluxCD Dependency Management - Thomas Morin & Francois Eleouet\, Orange
DESCRIPTION:Telecom companies are working together in the Sylva project to build a Kubernetes solution addressing their needs and letting them deploy 5G\, in particular on bare metal servers.\n\nSylva developers François Eleouet and Thomas Morin will share their experience on building Sylva\, developing on how Sylva leverages FluxCD unique fine-grained dependency management to assemble a fully declarative platform engineering solution.\n\nWe'll explain how GitOps with dependency management can bring predictability\, traceability and readability of operations\, on how a cluster and its workloads are deployed and upgraded.
CATEGORIES:FLUXCON
LOCATION:Elicium 1\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:e5bb3d68d6b9628fa23ada1324c1b542
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/e5bb3d68d6b9628fa23ada1324c1b542
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T111500Z
DTEND:20260323T112500Z
SUMMARY:⚡Lightning Talk: Airgap-native Identity Management: Lessons From Keycloak in DoD Deployments - Sebastian Łaskawiec & Michał Szynkiewicz\, Defense Unicorns
DESCRIPTION:In a world of constant connectivity\, air-gapped systems may feel like relics - yet they remain critical in defense\, national labs\, and high-assurance zones.\nIn this talk\, we invert the usual paradigm: focusing on the identity management problem space in a disconnected world. Starting with Zarf\, we’ll demonstrate how to construct sealed\, self-contained delivery bundles. We then dive deep into how we transformed Keycloak - from custom authentication and authorization flows with CAC\, to custom client policies\, and up to Client Authenticators for Kubernetes. Next\, we will explore how our platform meets DoD-level requirements\, such as securing the supply chain\, providing SBOMs\, and enabling full network lockdown with the help of Istio and Authservice.\nBy the end of the session\, you’ll have a tactical plan to deploy Keycloak in environments where “always online” is forbidden - and a hardened reference architecture you can apply to your next mission-critical deployment.
CATEGORIES:KEYCLOAKCON
LOCATION:Hall 7 | Room A\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:bab7eaa93f18f412673ba400ad7baa10
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/bab7eaa93f18f412673ba400ad7baa10
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T111500Z
DTEND:20260323T112500Z
SUMMARY:⚡Lightning Talk: Beyond ImagePullBackOff: A Stateless\, Secret-less Distributed Registry for Edge Workloads - Prasanth Baskar\, 8gearsAG
DESCRIPTION:We have all seen it. Your GitOps tool reports Synced in seconds\, but your edge node pods are stuck in ContainerCreating/ImagePullBackOff for minutes... hours. This is not just a low bandwidth problem. it is a fundamental design flaw. We are trying to apply a centralized\, cloud-native architecture to a decentralized\, distributed-systems problem.\n\nThis leads to slow startups\, failed updates even worse pullSecrets on every node create a massive security risk. In this session with Harbor Satellite (subproject of goharbor) we will run a stateless distributed registry along with your container workloads\n\nhttps://github.com/container-registry/harbor-satellite
CATEGORIES:KUBERNETES ON EDGE DAY
LOCATION:Emerald Room\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:430fd82fa0fe2c6186a8794b72cff611
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/430fd82fa0fe2c6186a8794b72cff611
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T111500Z
DTEND:20260323T112500Z
SUMMARY:⚡Lightning Talk: WasmPulse: Quantifying Wasm Sustainability With WASI Preview 2 Performance Numbers - Marcin Ziółkowski\, Orange
DESCRIPTION:As WebAssembly adoption grows\, it faces a critical performance data gap\, lacking the mature monitoring tools and standardized metrics of the container ecosystem\, especially regarding resource usage and sustainability. This talk introduces WasmPulse\, an open-source tool designed to fill that gap by providing CPU and Memory usage metrics for Wasm in a Prometheus-friendly format. &nbsp\;Stop guessing your resource usage\, and see what insights WasmPulse can provide to &nbsp\;become the “cAdvisor for WebAssembly” in your monitoring stack!\n\nWe'll also show Wasm's continuous improvement by providing highlights from our IEEE CCNC 2026 paper\, comparing bare-metal processes\, Containers\, and Wasm (AOT/JIT) on key metrics\, such as: artifact size\, startup time\, E2E network latency and CPU/Memory usage. The results position Wasm as an efficient\, performant and sustainable foundation for next-generation cloud-native platforms.\n\n
CATEGORIES:WASMCON
LOCATION:E106-108\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
