DTSTART:20260323T130500Z
DTEND:20260323T133000Z
SUMMARY:Quantum Proofing Sigstore: A Tale of Three Approaches - Kevin Conner & Firas Ghanmi\, Red Hat
DESCRIPTION:Implementing post quantum cryptography in supply chain security requires decisions beyond algorithm selection\, with trade offs impacting performance and storage. This talk explores three approaches for adding PQC into Sigstore\, the open standard for signing and verifying artifacts. The first implements hybrid X.509 certificates with dual classical/PQC signatures\, modifying signing\, verification and transparency components. The second maintains classical certificates\, adding PQC signatures to transparency log inclusion proofs. The third leverages merkle tree certificates\, embedding PQC commitments for efficient batch verification with minimal overhead. The talk presents prototypes\, demonstrates post quantum signing and verification\, reveals compromises in each approach and how assumptions in existing code created unexpected challenges. Attendees gain understanding of each method\, providing a foundation for contributing to community discussions around post quantum adoption.
CATEGORIES:OPEN SOURCE SECURITYCON
LOCATION:Hall 8 | Room D\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:0aabe4d1a0f7983c5871a257f5cd1aa6
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/0aabe4d1a0f7983c5871a257f5cd1aa6
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T131000Z
DTEND:20260323T133500Z
SUMMARY:Argo CD: Previewing Pull Request Changes in SECONDS! - Dag Bjerre Andersen\, Egmont & Sergey Shevchenko\, TangoMe
DESCRIPTION:As organizations increasingly adopt GitOps\, accurately visualizing manifest changes before they merge has become crucial.\n\nAt ArgoCon 2024 we presented a method that used ephemeral clusters to render precise diffs on pull requests - it was accurate but slow. This talk introduces a new approach that keeps the accuracy but reduces the wait time from minutes to seconds! Instead of spinning up a new cluster for every PR\, we connect each preview to a pre-configured Argo CD instance on standby.\n\nThe talk will showcase how this is used at Egmont to visualize manifest changes across repositories with hundreds of applications in just seconds\, and how developers at Tango integrate this technique into their CI/CD pipeline to preview changes to 1\,900 applications across 25+ clusters.\n\nThrough real-world examples\, Argo CD admins will learn how to set up accurate and fast diff previews on their pull requests\, resulting in faster code reviews\, shorter feedback loops\, and fewer failed deployments.
CATEGORIES:ARGOCON
LOCATION:G102-103\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:9a9423a4f1be62e63a8a41db46539484
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/9a9423a4f1be62e63a8a41db46539484
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T131000Z
DTEND:20260323T133500Z
SUMMARY:From Canary To Global: Unified Progressive Delivery for Hybrid Cloud With Karmada & Argo - Zhuang Zhang\, Huawei Technologies Co. Ltd & Ryan Wu\, Netease Cloud Music
DESCRIPTION:As enterprises adopt hybrid cloud and multi-cluster architectures for HA\, compliance\, and edge deployment\, application delivery grows complex. Manual cross-cluster progressive delivery is inefficient and risky. Most progressive delivery tools are single-cluster\, lacking global coordination.\n\nWe demonstrate how Karmada integrates with Argo CD and Argo Rollouts to build a unified hybrid-cloud progressive delivery platform—enabling "define once\, deliver safely anywhere": a single declarative spec drives consistent\, automated rollouts across all clusters. Now\, the platform is proven in production.\n\nIn this sharing\, we’ll go over:\n1. Key challenges and difficulties of progressive delivery in multi-cloud scenarios\;\n2. Problems and solutions in deploying and integrating Karmada and Argo\, as well as the amazing things they can achieve together\;\n3. Configuration details and overall workflow of Karmada and Argo in advanced deployment capabilities\, demonstrated through a canary release example.
CATEGORIES:ARGOCON
LOCATION:Auditorium\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:9541f9c36d3d7c9f53e0722cc514991f
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/9541f9c36d3d7c9f53e0722cc514991f
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T131000Z
DTEND:20260323T133500Z
SUMMARY:It Is Always DNS… Even at the Edge: Taming Proxy-Only Lookups With Cilium and eBPF - Hector Monsalve\, Roche & Thomas Gosteli\, TactumMotum GmbH
DESCRIPTION:Hoffmann-La Roche is leveraging the power of eBPF\, Cilium\, and Envoy to solve complex real-world DNS challenges in highly protected environments like laboratories and hospitals.\n\nGoing beyond basic connectivity\, we'll dive into our most recent edge networking hurdle: customer DNS resolvers explicitly block public domain resolution\, forcing all external lookups to occur exclusively through their HTTP forward proxies\, and how we overcame this constraint by leveraging Cilium's advanced network policy traffic redirect capabilities\, combined with some advanced CoreDNS filtering.\n\nWe will conclude with a live\, high-wire demonstration. If the demo gods are on our side\, you'll see these advanced Cilium features put into practice to instantly and reliably solve the DNS-over-Proxy challenge.
CATEGORIES:CILIUMCON
LOCATION:Elicium 1\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:ea49843b2ed7382f69058cb6f24946f3
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/ea49843b2ed7382f69058cb6f24946f3
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T131000Z
DTEND:20260323T133500Z
SUMMARY:Self-Healing Clusters: When Kyverno Writes Its Own Rules - Johan Heimar Prieto Benavides\, CursaCloud & Oscar Castillo\, Genius Sports
DESCRIPTION:What if your cluster could fix its own mistakes? In this talk\, we’ll share how we used Kyverno not only to enforce policies but to generate new ones based on real-time drift and audit feedback.\nBy analyzing repeated violations\, our platform automatically suggested corrective policies that operators could review and approve. The result: a self-evolving governance system where prevention improves itself over time.\nWe’ll discuss the architecture behind adaptive policies\, the telemetry pipelines that feed them\, and how this approach reduced incidents and configuration drift across multiple environments.
CATEGORIES:KYVERNOCON
LOCATION:E106-108\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:4b47277c6a28af83ed4f08a29ccf1ffb
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/4b47277c6a28af83ed4f08a29ccf1ffb
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T131000Z
DTEND:20260323T132000Z
SUMMARY:⚡Lightning Talk: Progress Over Purity: Sovereignty That Actually Ships - Antoine Tielbeke\, Team Rockstars IT
DESCRIPTION:My European server runs on Intel/AMD CPUs. Is that still "sovereign"? \n \n This lightning talk challenges the all-or-nothing mindset that paralyzes sovereignty initiatives. Building infrastructure for Volt Europa\, a pan-European political party with 35\,000 members\, taught me that meaningful progress beats ideological purity. \n \n The journey included uncomfortable discoveries: perfect sovereignty is impossible\, European providers have their own problems (our OVH cluster got billed in Polish Zloty with no easy way to migrate)\, and waiting for perfection means never starting. So we prioritized by impact\, migrating transactional email before marketing because it was critical and achievable. \n \n Three lessons in ten minutes: why portability matters more than perfection\, how to prioritize migrations pragmatically\, and why starting now beats waiting for the perfect provider. \n \n Stop demanding purity. Start making progress.
CATEGORIES:OPEN SOVEREIGN CLOUD DAY
LOCATION:F002-005\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:3aa4fabfe6af497fd625a5480f9ef088
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/3aa4fabfe6af497fd625a5480f9ef088
