BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTAMP:20260321T190205Z
DTSTART:20260323T134500Z
DTEND:20260323T141000Z
SUMMARY:Network Segmentation at Scale: GitOps-Driven Multi-Tenant Isolation With Argo CD - Luke Philips & Christian Hernandez\, Cisco
DESCRIPTION:Argo CD is built from the ground up with multitenancy in mind\, providing administrators with powerful tools needed to support many teams. However\, how does multitenancy work/look like when implemented? Production grade? This talk explores the complete picture: we will take you through all the considerations in building an isolated platform for multitenancy.\n\nWe will take a look on how to GitOps hundreds of tenants without creating network policy nightmare. Architectural patterns for tenant isolation using Cilium Network Policies managed through ArgoCD. ArgoCD Network Concerns and Best Practices. Tenancy with Projects and RBAC strategies for tenant self-service and compliance audit trails. Learn best practices\, common pitfalls\, and tested patterns from our real world experience running multi-tenant systems in production.
CATEGORIES:ARGOCON
LOCATION:G102-103\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:5f9f3044354ea40e6827f7a4fd51f991
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/5f9f3044354ea40e6827f7a4fd51f991
