SUMMARY:CiliumCon | Sponsored Keynote - Built in the Open: Why Cisco Is Betting on eBPF\, Cilium\, and Tetragon - Bill Mulligan\, Isovalent at Cisco
DESCRIPTION:The most important infrastructure standards of the next decade are being built in the open by communities\, code\, and ecosystems that scale far beyond any single product or platform.\n\nAt the core of this shift for Cisco are Cilium\, eBPF\, and Tetragon which are defining how networking\, security\, and observability are built in the multi cloud world. By investing upstream in Cilium\, eBPF\, and Tetragon\, Cisco is aligning product innovation with community driven standards ensuring that what runs in Kubernetes today can extend consistently across clouds\, data centers\, and the network itself.
CATEGORIES:CILIUMCON
LOCATION:Elicium 1\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:1b33209c1596e89c60182d651310feee
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/1b33209c1596e89c60182d651310feee
