SUMMARY:Beyond Vibecoding: The Coach/Player Model for Actual Autonomous Development - Douwe Osinga\, Block
DESCRIPTION:We introduce and demonstrate dialectical autocoding: a novel approach to AI-assisted software development that transcends the limitations of current vibe coding tools through a structured coach-player feedback loop. With a bounded\, adversarial process between two cooperating agents\, we show how AI can make substantially more progress on complex coding tasks\, resulting in better tested\, more robust outcomes\, while working around fundamental attention and human-in-the-loop limitations.\n\nBoth agents begin with the same goal: comprehensive requirements that describe the particulars of the problem. The requirements steer clear of implementation details or instructions\, save certain basic guidance such as choice of programming language/target platform\, allowing agents flexibility in arriving at its solution.\n\nWe believe this approach to cooperative autocoding is able to maintain goal persistence (long-horizon tasks with zero interruptions to humans that are directing the work.
CATEGORIES:AGENTICS DAY: MCP + AGENTS
LOCATION:Hall 7 | Room A\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:11d59d2f4d150d62eeaeaa85506f30a8
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/11d59d2f4d150d62eeaeaa85506f30a8
