SUMMARY:⚡Lightning Talk: The $10\,000 Argo CD Mistake: Eliminating Phantom Syncs and Scaling the Repo Server - Vanshika Jain\, Brudite Private Limited & Aditya Soni\, Sailpoint
DESCRIPTION:When your Argo CD setup grows to hundreds of applications\, things can go wrong in surprising ways. When you scale Argo CD to hundreds of applications (500+ and beyond)\, the Repo Server often becomes the biggest performance bottleneck.\nIt constantly polls Git repositories and regenerates manifests even when nothing has changed.\nThis leads to:\n• High CPU and memory usage\n• Slower syncs and reconciliations\n• Delayed deployments across teams\nIn this session\, we’ll share how we fixed it. We’ll walk through how to tune and scale the Argo CD Repo Server\, optimize Git polling\, and make Argo work smarter at scale\, how ApplicationSets can replace hundreds of repetitive configurations\, and how a few architectural shifts can make your GitOps setup faster and lighter
CATEGORIES:ARGOCON
LOCATION:G102-103\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
SEQUENCE:0
UID:2482f36d4ec7cad6e446d4c1eccca561
URL:http://colocatedeventseu2026.sched.com/event/2482f36d4ec7cad6e446d4c1eccca561
