SUMMARY:⚡Lightning Talk: Lessons from Putting AI in Front of a Platform: Taming the Non-Deterministic Beast - Shane Dowling\, Syntasso
DESCRIPTION:Agentic AI systems can do anything — and that’s the problem.\n \nIn this lightning talk\, Shane Dowling shares lessons learned from putting AI in front of a real developer platform. You’ll hear what happens when an MCP Server gets too much context\, why “more data” often means less control\, and how introducing structure and opinionated boundaries can transform chaotic AI behaviour into something useful and reliable. \nUsing experiments with Claude\, FastMCP\, and Kratix as a practical example\, Shane explores how to design safer\, more predictable agentic systems — and how to build interfaces where human and AI operators can actually collaborate productively. \nAttendees will leave with strategies for taming non-deterministic systems\, avoiding common pitfalls\, and designing the guardrails that let AI thrive safely in cloud-native environments.
CATEGORIES:PLATFORM ENGINEERING DAY
LOCATION:Hall 8 | Room G\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
