SUMMARY:⚡Lightning Talk: Securing AI Agents: Applying Service Mesh Patterns To MCP - Shriya Chaitanya Kamat Tarcar\, Nuvama Wealth Management Limited
DESCRIPTION:Although most MCP implementations lack basic authentication\, AI agents are being deployed with system-level permissions\, database access and API keys. Microservices security crisis is being recreated by the cloud native community but with agents capable of code modification\, data exfiltration and attack propagation.\n\nInformed by AI agent PoCs\,this talk will show how service mesh security patterns translate directly to MCP deployments.To demonstrate how mutual TLS authentication\, zero-trust boundaries and policy enforcement relate to inter-agent and agent-to-server communication\, this talk will look at MCP protocol specification\, Istio and Linkerd security models.\n\nAttendees will receive:1)Threat model that connects MCP attack vectors with locations in service mesh.2)Authentication patterns for MCP servers. 3)Framework for deploying security patterns.Before production deployments cause supply chain incidents\, session will provide the security foundation that agentic ecosystem needs.
CATEGORIES:AGENTICS DAY: MCP + AGENTS
LOCATION:Hall 7 | Room A\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
