SUMMARY:Open Sovereign Cloud Day | Closing Remarks - Thierry Carrez\, Program Committee Chair & Paula Grzegorzewska\, Program Committee Co-Chair
DESCRIPTION:The EC Cloud Sovereignty Framework (v1.2.1\, Oct 2025) is the definitive blueprint for EU digital autonomy. Born from Gaia-X and CIGREF\, it moves beyond standard security to address critical dependencies on non-EU actors and proprietary lock-in. \n \n In this session\, Emiel decodes the framework’s dual assessment approach: the Sovereignty Effective Assurance Level (SEAL) and the quantitative Sovereignty Score. We will break down the 8 Sovereignty Objectives (SOVs)—covering Legal\, Data/AI\, Supply Chain\, and Technology—and map the journey through the 5 SEAL levels toward Full Digital Sovereignty (SEAL-4). \n \n Crucially\, we will demonstrate why true sovereignty is impossible without open source. Attendees will learn how OSS directly enables the highest SEAL ratings and how "EU First" policies empower organizations to reclaim strategic control. This talk provides a clear roadmap for anyone navigating the future of sovereign digital procurement in Europe.
CATEGORIES:OPEN SOVEREIGN CLOUD DAY
LOCATION:F002-005\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
