SUMMARY:⚡Lightning Talk: How AI Agents Are Ending Interrupt-Driven Platform Work - Sunny Whang\, Cisco
DESCRIPTION:Platform engineers face relentless interrupts - supporting dozens of service owners while drowning in repetitive tickets for upgrades\, provisioning\, and troubleshooting. We built a multi-agent system at Outshift by Cisco to solve this internally. After proving its impact\, we open-sourced it as CAIPE: Community AI Platform Engineering (now part of CNOE) - because this pain point affects platform teams everywhere.\n\nThis talk shows how we achieved our deep supervisor agent that orchestrates complex tasks by coordinating sub-agents in parallel and sequential workflows. We use GraphRAG for internal platform knowledge and our OpenAPI MCP tool to rapidly integrate platform tools. Agents handle tasks from simple tickets to complex operations across ArgoCD\, Backstage\, Jira\, PagerDuty\, AWS\, and more.\n\nYou'll see our production demo\, architecture breakdown\, and practical lessons from deploying agents in production.
CATEGORIES:AGENTICS DAY: MCP + AGENTS
LOCATION:Hall 7 | Room A\, Amsterdam\, Netherlands
